article.headline: Wright St. 75, Northwd, Mich. 55
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Troy Tabler scored 17 points to lead Wright State past Northwood (Mich.) 75-55 on Wednesday night. Matt Vest and Vaughn Duggins added 11 points each for the Raiders (1-1), who shot 51.9 percent from the field (27 of 52), including 42.9 percent from the 3-point line (6 of 14). Tabler scored seven of his points in a 13-0 run that gave Wright State a 26-9 lead with 8:10 remaining in the first half. The Raiders led 44-29 at halftime, shooting 54.8 percent from the field (17 of 31) in the first half. Kegan Clark's jumper gave Wright State a 62-36 lead with 10:47 left in the game. Ten players scored for Wright State. The Raiders outrebounded Northwood 35-25 and outscored the Timberwolves 32-18 in the paint. Cameron Joyce and Andrew VanDierenDonck led Northwood (0-3), a Division II program, with 13 points each.
